                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Initial Consultation & Strategy</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">We discuss your specific situation, legal marriage regime, explore available options (e.g., mediation, contested litigation), and develop a strategic approach tailored to your needs and goals.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="flex items-start group">
                        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-rose-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform shadow-lg">
                            <i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="ml-6 flex-1">
                            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Drafting of Pleadings & Agreements</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-700">We prepare the divorce summons (or notice of motion for certain types of applications) and, if agreed, a comprehensive settlement agreement (also known as a consent paper) covering all aspects of the divorce, including children and finances.</p>
                        </div>
