                    <div id="faq1" class="px-6 py-5 hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 text-gray-800">
                        The duration of a divorce in South Africa depends significantly on whether it is uncontested or contested. An **uncontested divorce**, where both parties agree on all matters (property division, child care, contact, and maintenance), typically takes 6-12 weeks to finalize from the date of issue. **Contested divorces**, where there are unresolved disputes, can take 12-24 months or significantly longer, depending on the complexity of the issues, court availability, and whether parties are willing to settle.
