                            class="w-full text-left px-6 py-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-600 to-rose-600 text-white font-semibold focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pink-400 flex justify-between items-center hover:from-pink-700 hover:to-rose-700 transition-all"
                            onclick="toggleFAQ(event)">
                        <span class="pr-4">What factors determine child care and contact arrangements?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-300 text-2xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq2" class="px-6 py-5 hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 text-gray-800">
                        In all matters concerning children, South African courts apply the **"best interests of the child"** principle as paramount. Key factors considered include: the child's emotional and physical needs; the respective parenting abilities of each parent; the child's relationship with each parent and other significant persons; the child's own preferences (depending on age and maturity); and the desirability of maintaining stability and continuity in the child's life. Courts aim to maintain meaningful relationships with both parents where possible and appropriate.
