                        <span class="pr-4">How is child maintenance calculated in South Africa?</span>
                        <span class="transform transition-transform duration-300 text-2xl">▼</span>
                    </button>
                    <div id="faq3" class="px-6 py-5 hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 text-gray-800">
                        Child maintenance is calculated based on the child's reasonable needs and the respective financial means of both parents. There is no fixed formula, but courts determine the amount by assessing the child's expenses (e.g., food, clothing, housing, education, medical aid, extracurriculars) and then require each parent to contribute *pro rata* (proportionately) to those needs according to their income and expenses. The "Fohlmann formula" or similar guidelines may sometimes be used as a general reference, but it's not legally binding.
                    </div>
