                    <div id="faq4" class="px-6 py-5 hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-50 to-rose-50 text-gray-800">
                        In South Africa, all divorces must ultimately be granted by a High Court order. However, if you and your spouse reach a full agreement on all aspects of the divorce (property, child care, contact, maintenance), this is known as an **uncontested divorce**. In such cases, you will typically only need to make one brief appearance in court for the final hearing. Mediation and collaborative divorce are excellent ways to resolve disputes out of court before the final court appearance.
